**Managing User Interface of a project in Eclipse Dirigible**

In this tutorial you will learn how to manage the User Interface (UI) of your project.

**Prerequisites**

You should have an existing project in Eclipse Dirigible.

**Context**

- Generating a Web Page
- Creating an Index Page
- Adding the index page to the main menu of your web page

**Procedure for generating a web page.**

1. In the _Workspace Explorer_, expand _ScriptingServices_, then your project folder. Select the entity.
2. Select _Generate -\&gt; UI for Entity Service._
3. Select _the List Entities template_, then all current available fields.
4. Name your file and the page title.



**Index Page**

**Procedure for creating an index page.**

1. In the _Workspace Explorer_, select _WebContent_.
2. Select _New -\&gt; UI_.
3. Choose the _Index Page_ ption and then choose **Next**.
4. Name your page title and choose **Finish**.
5. In the _WebContent_ open the _main_._menu_ file in a new tab.
6. Add previously generated page in the descriptor of the main menu – change name and link.
7. Save all changes.

You have successfully generated a web page, an index page and have added it to your project.

To preview your page, select the _index.html_ file, then open the link in a separate browser tab.
